From a7d10fc2a2da84b1b58769a2bdc0d0897bc15cf6 Sat May 23 13:04:36 2020 +0530
From: Sathishkumar Muruganandam <murugana@codeaurora.org>
Date: Sat May 23 13:04:36 2020 +0530
Subject: ath11k: fix sta signal value update in station dump

Ath11k updates the sinfo->signal in sta_statistics from the
arsta->rssi_comb value of the corresponding sta.

This rssi_comb is updated from ppdu_info coming from monitor status
ring. Currently this update is not happening due to fc_valid and
invalid ast_index check.

These checks were added only for the issue of UL-OFDMA stats not
getting updated properly and are valid only when END_USER_STATS is
enabled on Rx filter of HTT stats (via ext_rx_stats).

Hence moving the checks only for non-SU cases and allow MU stats
to get updated along with ext_rx_stats enabled.

Added back below fixes which caused regression.

1. Assign default HTT Rx filter to update properly in
   ath11k_mac_config_mon_status_default().

2. Update NL80211_STA_INFO_SIGNAL flag in
   ath11k_mac_op_sta_statistics() for proper station dump signal
   value.

Tested the fix on IPQ8074 and IPQ6018 platforms to be working.

Change-Id: I52e7f59e57d73e5a01cfa966e182209642e0e8ad
Signed-off-by: Sathishkumar Muruganandam <murugana@codeaurora.org>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_rx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_rx.c
@@ -5659,15 +5659,13 @@ int ath11k_dp_rx_process_mon_status(stru
 			goto next_skb;
 		}
 
-		if ((ppdu_info.fc_valid) &&
-				(ppdu_info.ast_index != HAL_AST_IDX_INVALID)) {
-			if (ppdu_info.reception_type == HAL_RX_RECEPTION_TYPE_SU) {
-				arsta = (struct ath11k_sta *)peer->sta->drv_priv;
-				ath11k_dp_rx_update_peer_su_stats(arsta, ppdu_info);
-			} else {
-				ath11k_dp_rx_mon_process_ulofdma(ppdu_info);
-				ath11k_dp_rx_update_peer_mu_stats(ar, ppdu_info);
-			}
+		if (ppdu_info->reception_type == HAL_RX_RECEPTION_TYPE_SU) {
+			arsta = (struct ath11k_sta *)peer->sta->drv_priv;
+			ath11k_dp_rx_update_peer_su_stats(arsta, ppdu_info);
+		} else if ((ppdu_info->fc_valid) &&
+				(ppdu_info->ast_index != HAL_AST_IDX_INVALID)) {
+			ath11k_dp_rx_mon_process_ulofdma(ppdu_info);
+			ath11k_dp_rx_update_peer_mu_stats(ar, ppdu_info);
 		}
 
 		if (ath11k_debugfs_is_pktlog_peer_valid(ar, peer->addr)) {
